1. Remove Panel
2. Add Application Menu Bar
3. Add System Tray Widget
4. Add Application Menu Widget
5. Add digital clock Menu Widget
6. Add Spacer and order stuff
7. Add shortcut key to the Application Menu widet by right clicking on it and adding a shortcut alt + F1
8. Add Latte dock sudo apt install latte-dock
put zoom on hover to 70, background to 40
9. Add application dashboard to latte-dock, drag and drop it on the dock
10. Add Application Title widget and add it to the to top application menu pannel.

#Themeing
1. Add Icons
2. Add Themes you like
3. Add blur in application style
4. Change window decorations. I added MCMojave styles.
5. Set Application Style in GNOME/GTK Application Style to Breeze-Dark
This will change GNOME/GTK applications themes to change

#Desktop Effect
1. Go to Workspace Behavior/Desktop Effects ->  Enable Magic Lamp
                                                Enable Wobbly Windows
                                                Enable Sheet
                                                
2. Change Wallpaper
3. Change Lockscreen Appearance

#Terminal Theming
1. You can add new color schemes easily in Appearance menu
